<p>A conversation in Spoonerian, a language conducted entirely in spoonerisms, <a href="https://archive.org/details/wordrecreationsg0000eckl/page/128/mode/2up">proposed by J.A. Lindon</a>:</p>
<p>A: Hot woe, Barley Chinks!<br />
B: Hot woe, Chilly Base!<br />
A: Blocking showy, Miss Thorning.<br />
B: Glowing a bale.<br />
A: It slacked one of my crates.<br />
B: I&#8217;ve a late slacking. The drain rips in.<br />
A: Porter on the willows? Tut-tut!<br />
B: Mad for the bite. Cuddles on the pot.<br />
A: A very washy splinter.<br />
B: All blood and mowing.<br />
A: Here&#8217;s to spray in the Ming!<br />
B: Sadsome glummer! &#8216;Ware fell!<br />
A: Low song!</p>
